<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0006" RecordId="021-000000002"><Name>Riaccesi (Accademia dei)</Name><AlternativeName>Accademia dei Ravvivati|Congrega dei Riaccesi</AlternativeName><City CityId="1"><CityItalianName>Bologna</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Bologna</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Bononiae</CityLatinName></City><EmblemDescription>Torch extinguished by a fountain</EmblemDescription><EmblemImage ImageId="52618">021-000000002_52618_1.jpg</EmblemImage><Motto>Un fiato sol che spira</Motto><StartDate>ca 1560; ca.1619</StartDate><EndDate>before1686</EndDate><DateText>ca 1560; ca.1619-before1686</DateText><Notes>Created in the second half of the 16th century as Accademia degli Accesi. Restored ca 1619 as Accademia dei Ravvivati, with motto `Un fiato sol che spira`, and emblem representing `Burning logs, blown on by a wind`  (see Branchi`s Clorinda). From 1636 it was called Accademia dei Riaccesi, with the above motto and emblem. Possibly, the following volume - not in British Library collections - belongs to this Academy: Costante Accademico Travagliato, Lagrime del Reno di Bologna rime funebri, nella infelicissima morte dell`illustre sig. conte Andalo Bentivogli vcciso a caso giostrando. Del Costante Academico Trauagliato (In Bologna: per Vittorio Benacci, 1590). </Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5100" RecordId="022-000000097"><Name>Abelli, Cesare, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5202" RecordId="022-000000196"><Name>Guastavillani, Filippo, Senator, </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5371" RecordId="022-000000378"><Name>Bolognini, Donino, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5372" RecordId="022-000000381"><Name>Cerva, Angelo Vincenzo, , </Name><Nickname>Academico Ravvivato</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5373" RecordI